Sadio Mane scored twice as Liverpool beat Manchester City 3-2 in a classic FA Cup semi-final at Wembley and kept alive their quadruple hopes. Ibrahima Konate opened the scoring after nine minutes before Mane netted a bizarre goal, tackling City keeper Zack Steffen on the goalline. Mane added his second with a thunderous volley before the break.   EPL: Ronaldo hat-trick earns Man Utd win against Norwich     Akure High Chief arraigned for allegedly duping Ondo     Over 90% sponsoring insecurity in Imo are Christians –…   Jack Grealish scored for City shortly after the restart and Bernardo Silva added another in the 91st minute. But Liverpool held on to reach their 15th FA Cup final.BBC